Ok I drive Uber to make money to survive. I am not the fake it till you make it guy.
I like antiques. Blame momma for that. I love things of beauty. Im not rich enough to say everything has a price but one day I hope to be able to order off a menu and not even look at prices.
I am just a regular guy who swims in the pond of eclectic people and damn proud of it.

@angelalevin1 Angela, I so love you, every time you critique Meghan, you get it 100% right! What an awful woman she is.

@TrevorCoult_MC @matthewdmarsden @ptsdresolution I love your tweets and the awareness you raise for ptsd and veterans. I read out to my husband in the car, you had a brewery voucher and wanted to give it away to deserving vets, we were both touched. Keep up the good work.
@according2_taz I just want to let you know that I love your videos on you tube. You are always so upbeat and funny, and your content on The Harkles is spot on! Don’t change.

Poll: Do You Like Or Dislike Meghan, Duchess of Sussex? Vote NOW: https://t.co/KohoOAR8fQ

@danwootton Hi Dan, my godmother and her Kiwi husband moved back to NZ 23 years ago. We speak at least 3 times a week. Our main conversations involve Harry, Meghan and Jacinda. We can’t stand any of them. We look forward to your comments and observations and find you always so spot on!
@michellevisage Hi Michelle, my husband and I thought you were fantastic hosting EPOS. So much so that we hope the BBC snap you up.
@angelalevin1 Angela, I always listen to your interviews and read your comments. You are so fair and wise. You were great on GMB this morning.
@The_JamesJordan I’ve always loved you as you are so honest and speak your mind. You don’t suffer fools. I know what it is like to lose your Dad, keep strong.
@EamonnHolmes I hope they sort you out very soon. You deserve some respite as you have been so supportive of others in pain x

@EamonnHolmes Hi Eamonn, how are you now? I know this may seem a silly question, but, have you taken a couple of pain tablets, they might make you feel a little drowsy and help you go back to sleep. I recently purchased a hospital bed that can go up and down at various angels, that may help?

@EamonnHolmes Hi Eamonn, you suggested to me a couple of nights ago about sharing our experiences we go through with our pain during the night, and I more than happy to share with anyone struggling. I am normally awake during the early hours of the morning, so please feel free to chat x

@EamonnHolmes What a great idea, especially as it feels so lonely and the nights so long before daylight. I am in my 60,s and think you should be on the TV more as you speak for us older generation who cannot abide this woke world, particularly with the unpalatable Meghan and Harry!

@EamonnHolmes I have been awake since 2.00am as I have an illness that mirrors MS, which causes neuropathy and is very uncomfortable. I have seen your tweets before in the early hours and my heart goes out to you. I have always been a fan, thank you for thinking of others.

@piersmorgan This is the first tweet I have ever done(I am 62),but, feel so strongly about this appalling interview. I, and all my friends and family are 100% with you. You speak the real truth on behalf of all of us. Thank you, please don’t ever change.
